Package com.github.hotware.lucene.extension.bean.type

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AnyClassType
    Types that can handle all classes.
    SingularFieldType
    types that store their stuff in a singular field (that can still have multiple values, but most of the time the already supported Set and List are sufficient)
    Type
    the main extension point for providing different types to handle in Lucene Beans

    For slightly easier usage use BaseSingularType
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BaseSingularType  
    MultiFieldType
    a MultiFieldType can have its information spread into more than one field in the document. this is done by writing a StoredField with =.
    StockType
    Inner classes of this type contain basic Types that are shipped with the extension.
    StockType.BooleanType  
    StockType.DoubleStringType  
    StockType.DoubleType  
    StockType.FloatStringType  
    StockType.FloatType  
    StockType.IntegerStringType  
    StockType.IntegerType  
    StockType.LongStringType  
    StockType.LongType  
    StockType.SerializeType
    the index attribute is ignored, as these Serialized Types can only be stored to be retrieved afterwards.
    StockType.StringType
